HEADWORD: Sinful
<hw>Sin"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AAS.
<ets>synfull</ets>.]</ety> <def>Tainted with, or full of, sin; wicked;
iniquitous; criminal; unholy; <as>as, <ex>sinful</ex> men;
<ex>sinful</ex> thoughts</as>.</def> <rj><au>Piers
Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ah <qex>sinful</qex> nation, a people laden with iniquity.</q>
<rj><qau>Isa. i. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sin"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sin"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sing</ent>⟦br⟧
